messages.content: You arise from your slumber in your EVIL apartment complex. It is a weekday, meaning you are expected to show up to the zoo. You may show up on time, giving you more time to prepare, yet also you may show up slightly late to torment them. Decisions, decisions…

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl takes in the scenery of her apartment and begins a small maniacal chuckle to herself. "Those fools that allow me to live here don't even realize what they've done, do they? It's only a matter of time before I, Voreverl Leocot, can finally reveal the machinations I've been brewing here. Soon I'll have all the minions I need to enact my scheme... Haah, but for now, I, Voreverl Leocot, must attend to the first step of this master scheme." Voreverl gets up from bed and checks her apartment for cereal

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Voreverl has some cereal stored in her apartment.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Good... Good... With this level of proper supply stocking, running an evil organization from the shadows will be little more than a single step up the evil staircase of doom." Voreverl pours herself a bowl of Trix, her favorite cereal, due to the kids who cruelly torture the rabbit being a strong inspiration for her as a child. After finishing, she prepares herself for work and heads out as soon as she can, as it's important to maintain appearances so her betrayals can sting harder

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
At the front gate, Voreverl encounters her boss.
“…You’re five minutes late. Whatever. Eric is over by the flamingos, see if he needs help. I’ll bug you when I need something.”
She’s preoccupied with her phone at the moment.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Heh, sorry about my tardiness, evil simply runs in a different time zone, to stay ahead of any who get in our way." Voreverl heads over to the flamingos, spending her time on the way to them wondering what the best way to win over their loyalty would be.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Hi Voreverl! Hi.” Eric is dressed entirely in pink, lugging around a bucket of shrimp.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Greetings, Eric. Heheheh, I see you've prepared an outfit today that will truly make anyone who looks upon it despair, quite the genius tactic for a betrayal... Although I'm sad I didn't think of it first, this challenge will only serve to make my future schemes that much stronger."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Haha, yeah.” Eric nods over enthusiastically, as if to put his all into conveying that he really understands what you’re saying.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Well then, the 'boss' wished for me to check if you needed my assistance, which I'll be happy to provide. After all, I'm still a loyal member of this zoo's staff, and clearly always will be." The edges of Voreverl's mouth unconsciously form a smirk as she says the last part of her statement.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: :smirkhuman:

author.name: legoskelton
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\7324d6b2e5e7b2d85c445c799b852d80-F5E1E.png

messages.content:
“Well, I appreciate any help! But…” He looks over your outfit. “Well, okay, this isn’t strictly a thing I was TOLD to do, but I think it’s good for these guys development if they’re able to view the source of their food as one of their own, so…” he gestures to his outfit.

“I like animals.” He smiles and gives a thumbs up. “Uh, it looks like this won’t be enough, some of these guys haven’t even gotten any yet. Could you grab another bucket from the back room?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
"One of their own..." Voreverl is shocked, her mind racing, was that the missing ingredient that her concoction of schemes needed all this time? To allow her minions to view her as one of them? No, no, that can't be it, can it? How can you maintain a sense of authority then... She'll have to think about this carefully.

"Oh, uh!" Voreverl snaps out of her train of thought "Right, thanks for the advice, I'll keep it in mind. One bucket of disposable sea minions coming up." Voreverl heads to the backroom to look for a shrimp bucket.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: You find the bucket, but receive a call via CELLULAR PHONE just as you do.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "This better be important, I can't allow myself to be distracted from a job as crucial as this. If I don't win over these animals quick enough, the government is sure to catch onto me, even those fools have their limits. One arrest is enough for a villain origin story, I don't need another." Voreverl answers the call.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: "Hello, you've reached the aspiring evil mastermind Voreverl Leocot, what insignificant pawn am I speaking to?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: You hear a deep sigh on the other end of the line. “It’s your father, Jane. …Are you still in Italy?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl's voice gets caught in her throat for a moment as she hears this, and pauses for a few seconds before responding "...G- Gweheheh! So you've been tracking my movements, have you, father? Indeed, Italy is the center of all my current schemes. I've wormed my way into organizations the power of which you wouldn't even be able to dream of! I'm really quite busy, due to my success, so what is it that you want?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: There is a substantial pause before you receive a reply. “…Okay. Your mother will be in the area soon. I’m not sure if she intends to visit you or not, but I guess I should let you know ahead of time. I don’t support this… ‘lifestyle’, but…” He trails off.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl does an exaggerated shrugging pose for no one in particular "I wouldn't expect someone like you to get it, no, it's better that you don't. A mastermind is nothing without a society to overturn, after all. But, uh, thanks for letting me know, I suppose. I'm sure mother will be utterly *delighted* to see where I've ended up."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Yeah, good, okay. Just… keep your head up. You’re a Leiblich, whether we can see eye to eye or not. Don’t let yourself become someone else’s pawn.” He hangs up without letting you respond to this.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl's hand tightens around her phone "...Me? A pawn? Hah! Who does he think I am!? And what's with that 'Jane' and 'Leiblich' crap!? Asshole knows that's not my name! Ugh, whatever, soon he won't be able to go anywhere without seeing my real name covering the news! First this zoo, then the world, and he'll see!" Voreverl angrily grabs the bucket and heads back to Eric, grumbling to herself.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Eric waves. “Thanks!” He takes the bucket.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Well, I'm glad *someone* appreciates my efforts. All things considered, there's certainly worse minions I could've gotten than you. Perhaps I can put off my planned betrayal for a few more days than I had it scheduled. I need the time to figure out how to steal the beanie anyway."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Eric clutches his hat possessively.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl chuckles to herself for a moment, before changing to a more serious expression and shifting her gaze "...Hey, Eric. Do you have a family?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Eric tenses up.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: “Well… everyone does. But I guess I’m as close as you can get to not having one. We aren’t on speaking terms. I have too much family, one might say.” He lightens up, returning to lovable old Eric Zeety. “Any reason you ask?”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I- Uh, well, I was just..." Voreverl balls her hands into fists, digging her nails into her hand "I was wondering who I'd hold for ransom if you turned against me! That's it, yeah! What a shame that you're not too close to them, guess there goes that evil scheme!"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Eric laughs. “That’s Voreverl, alright. Literally never stops with the fantastic jokes.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "It's not a joke! Ugh, maybe I was wrong about your usefulness as a minion. Can't even recognize a genuine evil genius right in front of you. I can only hope there's not more people like you out there, the thought of my first official announcement of my evil intentions on a global scale being met with laughter..." Voreverl shivers

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Personally, I think the best jokes are those that contain elements of sincerity.” Eric strokes his chin thoughtfully.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Well if you have such deep thoughts on comedy, I'm sure you'll enjoy your role as a court jester in my evil empire. Actually, are court jesters even still a thing? The internet might've phased them out. Maybe my evil empire can have, like, an official TikTok or something. Yes, yes, win the public over using their own means of entertainment, make them slaves to our comedy. I'll have to look into this."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: “Yeah.” Eric exits the flamingo enclosure into the publicly accessible walkways.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl continues mumbling about her schemes as she moves on to do whatever else is in her job description.

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Does anything else occur at Voreverl or is it an uneventful day at the zoo

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Very strange, but you are approached by a young woman and roll insight

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content: Sure. Anyway,

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
She walks up to you. "...That would be it, then. Right among the filthy animals where you belong."

Eric is nearby. "Hey, what's uh, going on?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl is taken off guard for a moment "Huh? Ah, sorry, I was deep in thought on how to win these animals over, trying to build up some minions for my empire, you see. Good to hear that someone else agrees that this is the ideal spot for building up my followers! Animals truly are the easiest to manipulate."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
Eric smiles. "You really do have a way with words, wow."

The woman twitches, then takes a deep breath. "I'm a patient, mature person. I'll hold back from giving you what you deserve if you stop making the act of speaking with you feel like pulling teeth."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Pulling teeth..." Voreverl contemplates this image for a moment "Heheheh, so my machinations are that effective, then? The betrayal of losing one's pearly whites, a mouth unable to chew on its prey. Indeed, an apt comparison for what all civilians will feel after my conquest! You really understand what this is all about."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
She pauses, and fiddles with something you can roll perception for. "You don't even know, do you? Of course. Can't be bothered to think of anyone but yourself."

Eric is uncomfortable.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((14 for perception)) "Heh, that's an odd thing to say. I know everything that I need to, and don't bother with anything that won't progress my goals. Other people are just there to fuel my evil conquest or get in its way. So then, you might want to stop acting so superior if you want anything resembling a respectable position in the world once it's under my rules. Pfft, just kidding, I could never stick to such a deal."

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
"Hey, Voreverl's a little different from other people, but just because she's all evil doesn't mean she's a bad guy!" Eric speaks out defensively.

Voreverl is perceptive enough to note that the girl has put on brass knuckles. "Try me, Jane. Go ahead. What else do you have to say?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Voreverl takes a step back "Ah, hey, uh, whoa there, hold on. I don't think you understand who you're challenging, there's no way that someone as simpleminded as- Wait, Jane? Do I know you from somewhere?"

author.name: natyobb
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\ba6cc976522571d97f7cf7d74d5b3684-FF145.png

messages.content:
Voreverl gets punched in the face. In the real world, there are no initiative rolls.

The girl flinches from the impact and asks you something about some person, but you can't make out the name. Eric runs up to her angrily and grabs her by the collar.

You lose consciousness.

messages.content:
Viotto comes upon the construction site he has visited before.

“Oh, Christ.” The man currently nailing down planks groans at your arrival.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
Ah, a fine replacement for a park indeed. He despises this place... the smell of wood dust in the air, so ready to trigger a dust explosion should there be any electrostatic discharge. Viotto glances around at the power tools filling the air with their disgusting noise, powered by these disgusting people. They have no care for anyone but themselves and their own pockets.
Wafting his way over to the center of the construction site, he raises both of his hands magnanimously into the air. 
"Hello once again, people of this beautiful country! This work you do... it is the cornerstone of our society, isn't it? We humans, we take on this endeavor... of inching across the land provided to us by God, expanding and rebuilding our communities, putting our blood, sweat, and tears into these projects, purely for the sake of those around us! That you would construct these things that you may never use, it is the ultimate sign of selflessness. You fantastic people!"

messages.content:
As he peers down at the words, his expression hardens.
"It has been said that the problem with being yourself is that you've been given the responsibility for all your own flaws. Maybe I'm the one who said that, come to think of it. Ha! But perhaps it's the opposite. The people around you are the ones you are truly able to rely on for help, for correction. Isn't that what a community really is? Isn't that what people say? And I would have to agree... community is often where people as flawed as yourself can remind you of how *sick* you truly are."
Viotto stares off around the construction site, his eyes filled with rage. This is obviously also part of the rehearsed speech.
Suddenly, his gaze fix back on that lone worker.
"And yet, after all this time spent with those of your ilk, you still remain as fucking impenetrable as ever. Endless, endless reinforcement! And you gain nothing of it! And so I ask, is it not necessary to take a side path? Who else is around you all?!"
He sweeps a hand dramatically in front of him.
"Aha! None other than I, Entenmann! Everyone must leave their proverbial comfort zone, take advice from those better than them in any way they may find. You know, believing oneself to be perfect is the sign of delusion - and what do those delusions lead to?! Danger! Danger for those around you, for those you truly love and depend on! That danger we are so ill-prepared for, obsessed as we are with probability!"

messages.content:
As he walks home, he contemplates his day so far. It was very productive! That worker seemed to really get his message, and he ended up with the pamphlet. I'm sure he can work things out, regardless of how abhorrent he may be from a moral standpoint. These ideas are just self-evident at a certain point.
He comes across his beautiful home. He steps over the doormat, through the front door, and smiles. There's nowhere he'd rather be. We all have to push ourselves sometimes, but having a place to come back to, a place where love resides, makes it all worthwhile. He finds his favorite chair, and leans back.
His spine hits the cold, metal wall. He adjusts the stack of flame retardant plastic sheeting he's sitting on, and half-closes the lid of the dumpster. He made it nearly an hour this time, he thinks. He still needs to go out and find something to fill his empty stomach, but for now, he can just... write.

messages.content: He sighs. "Sorry, sorry, I don't mean to be rude. I was just taking a moment away from this h- uh, this strenuous world. You know it takes its toll on me sometimes."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He backs away. “That’s… alright. I know you value having some solitude. I’ve got the same sort of need.”

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "I'm sure you do, Deltent."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "What can I help you with on this fiiiine morning? I do recall owing you a favor for that assistance earlier."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He pauses. "Well, if you're offering... I guess an answer. Even now I still don't understand, and I don't want to let my chance to know slip by. You were a big deal. I might have exaggerated how closely affiliated I was with you, but I sure as hell knew who Viotto Entenmann was. But you gave it all up. Why? Did you change your mind about it being the path for you?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Viotto considers for a moment. "I'm just not quite sure what you mean by changing my path... my path has not changed in the s-slightest. I have gone from protecting the innocent to protecting the innocent, arguably in the same way as ever. Prevention is simply infinitely more important than response, and I've chosen to get my priorities straight. Fire doesn't put off smoke until it's already burning, you know..."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "I may not have a satisfying answer for you if I can't understand the question!" he chuckles.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He leans back against the inside of the dumpster. It calms him.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "I guess I can understand. Even if I still can't ignore the feeling that something must've happened." Sheeval leans against a wall. "If you didn't wake up tomorrow, and you were conscious in an out of body experience for some time to take in this fact, would you be satisfied with the life you lived? ...A weird question, I'm sorry."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
"An odd way to phrase a question about the afterlife. Regardless... I don't think this is a question I can ever truly answer. Can anyone? The point of judging our actions on this Earth is to change the way that we may act in the future. If that gets cut off, I have no idea how I would view the morality of things anymore. There's a finality that I don't have the virtue of at the moment. That's all I can say."
Viotto's eyes indicate a different answer. They're regretful.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: Sheeval notices his expression, and is silent for a moment. "Yeah... as usual, you make your case well, even if I don't see it the same way. It's a hypothetical I think about a lot, the age I am. I still don't know if I've done enough to make my impact on the world a net positive. If what I'm doing even matters. It's just... I want to do *something*. I wish I could've decided on a purpose as committed as you have."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Unfortunately, Deltent, I have no idea what you do, or what your impact on the world is. I am in no place to reassure you, because the only thing I ever seem to see you do is follow me around. Did you *actually* work with me? I admit, my memory is going a bit, but not so much that I would forget a co-worker. I remember everything about that clinic, and I *do not* remember you."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: His regretful look becomes slightly more challenging.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: Sheeval shrugs. "...Yeah, I was never really a fan of that story. It relies on you being forgetful, which is a little ridiculous. It was a lie. I was still at university during your heyday."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
"I see. A con artist as well as an intermittent stalker. If I did not find solace in us being so close in social status and age, and indeed, former profession, I do not think I would be able to tolerate you. But it is admittedly a good pairing. Two old men, abandoned by the world around them. It makes me wonder how you ended up here, but I would never be so *prying* as to ask."
Viotto senses that he's becoming bitter again. He tries his hardest to reserve that for his speeches. He quickly changes the subject to make sure Sheeval doesn't respond to the accidentally implied question anyways. 
"Any interest in trying to find some food with me?" He assumes that Deltent is on *protection sociale*, so he doubts that he would accept.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "...Sure. Though I suppose while I clear the air I should admit I'm not actually completely destitute. Still homeless, but not without means. We can eat like, an actual meal, if you'd like."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Viotto is drawing a blank. He has no idea if this is allowed under his system of ethics. After staring blankly at Sheeval for around 10 minutes, he slowly draws in a breath, and says "Sure."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Lead the way."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: Sheeval Deltent and Viotto Entenmann have a meal that is not quite breakfast, nor is it lunch, at the local McDonald's. It is an unforgettable experience that was not planned on happening.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Viotto spends the entire time scribbling in his notebook.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: It's clear this was his plan from the start.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: ((you've barely touched your nuggies dear...))

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "This is what life is about. True luxury lies in simply having the means to survive without worry." Sheeval Deltent is saying some wild shit. He's just so emotionally affected by the burger quality.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Viotto feels looked down upon. He tries his hardest to ignore his gracious host.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He reaches up and grabs a nuggie.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: It's pretty good.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Uh, no offense, or anything. I'm just happy to be here."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Viotto realizes that he's out of sauce. He mumbles something about it and stands to head to the sauce counter, not looking up from his notebook of speeches. "Maybe a... no, that's not... really intimidating enough... hm."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He checks to see if they have any Szechuan sauce this time of year.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: Unfortunately, they do not.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Sheeval frowns. "This establishment isn't that great.... no sauce at all."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Fine dining indeed, Deltent. Remind me why you dragged me out here? Is there something you wished to accomplish, or were you simply taking pity on me for my lack of acquiescence to the government's handouts?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Whatever. Unless you have some objection, I'm taking my nuggets back home. This has been far too much stimulation for me. Tell McDonald to turn his lights down next time."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "No, you just... well, okay. It was nice. Stay safe." He waves.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Viotto waves back, smiling broadly. The smile is hidden by the scarf that he's pulled back up.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He starts making his way back home, one more time. There is no longer a pressing need for food. He considers going to a park like he had originally planned, though... he has much more success there than at that blasted construction site.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: Weighing it in his head, he decides that he has enough energy to give it a shot.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He arrives at the park. There's a few people there.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
He looks for a suitable place to stand, finding a nice patch of grass near the center. He sweeps his jacket around, sticks his hand out in front of him, and generally tries his hardest to be dramatic. His other hand appears from his pocket discreetly holding a scrap of paper, shoots forward, and just like at the construction site, he raises them with an energy of magnanimity.
"Tell me, folks!" he says loudly. "Can even one of you here spell out your own ideology?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He waits desperately for a response that he can use.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: There is a long gap before someone responds. "I consider myself a libertarian."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
An incredibly non-specific answer, and not even a solid political party in France. This is better than he could have hoped for. "Ah, I see. Such a specific answer, such a solid choice for a Frenchwoman! And yet, where does that specificity lie...? Tell me. Which way does this go for you; did you decide each and every moral quandary for yourself and just *happened* to land in a place where you can use such a unifying word on yourself? Or did you start from a place of identification with libertarianism, and their philosophies gradually convinced you, brought about change? I bet I can guess, judging by the sorry state of our political affairs."
He looks coldly at the people around him.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "We divide ourself into these... roles. It's quite fascinating, isn't it? You are a libertarian, I am a proselytizer, these people are bystanders, there are... doctors, police, firefighters, name anything. When asked to take preventative medicine, is our first thought 'this well never be important to me, because doctors exist to save me'? When we are told that locking our doors at night is a protective measure, do we say, 'the police will be there to save me when I get robbed'? The answer is obvious, and yet curious all the same."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "We humans... we're obsessed with... probability. What is the chance of something bad happening to me? How can I lower it? And you, as a, um, uh, a libertarian, you... well, you... prioritize freedom over danger... or... well..."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He starts violently stumbling over his words as he attempts to personalize the speech. This is his least favorite part of doing Q&A segments.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Look, let me get... back on track... I..." He flips through his notes a bit.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Yes! Probability! We are so obsessed with probability, and yet, I believe it was Albert Einstein who once said, "God does not play dice with the universe". If God is in no position to obsess over these things, how can we be superior to Him? It's preposterous."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: ((albert einstein officially represented in q&a lfgggg))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((i mean tap. but also this viotto q&a of course))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "People... they treat life as a 'mystery' to be 'solved.' And yet, does this not defeat itself?  There are two approaches to a situation, you could say. React as events occur, or anticipate them in advance. To turn a life into this game is… to take the latter option, and in some way mold it into something self-contained, something unfettered by whatever result it's trying to achieve. To figure out the cause of something… what is it for? To avoid danger. But that isn't how you avoid danger in the real world, by funneling yourself down the most narrow, singular expectation of what to avert. You do it by FEARING danger, whether your empty head considers it the *solution* or not! To miscalculate is to throw yourself off of the scent of preparation, and we humans are so prone to miscalculation that some would call it our defining characteristic. No… a fire doesn't put off smoke until after it's too late. When you view life in such ways, you must accept the fact that the clues are nothing more than tragedies themselves."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: He thrusts his cane at the libertarian, his signature move.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Tell me, daughter of God. What would you do as the flames roared around you?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: The libertarian, having been designated as female, responds "I think there is no God. So your argument falls apart there, unfortunately." She does not respond to all ten other paragraphs she politely stood through.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: Viotto is a bit perturbed. "Allow me to reach my point, then. What I said earlier about roles... did you understand my meaning? When we are told we can take further preventative steps in fire safety, in electrical safety, it is too easy to think, 'this is what firefighters are for - SAVING me'. And yet, salvation is the *opposite of what your goal should be.* Salvation is something that inherently assumes that you have lost, that you have given up. Humans rely on those around them? Pah. Such a statement is one dreamed up by the deranged to push responsibility onto some blind scapegoat. Relying on others is deferral. And deferral is death. This is something every man must understand. Do you see my point? What would you use your freedom for if not this? True salvation is... the avoidance of the need for salvation. I'm sure a non-religious person such as yourself would have to agree, no?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Tell me this. If you didn't wake up tomorrow, and you were conscious in an out of body experience, would you be satisfied with the improvements you had made to the world around you? The ways in which you had prevented others from coming to harm by your own carelessness, your own obsession with roles, with deferral?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: She considers this for a moment. "I'd probably haunt some people."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: He frowns. "That was not part of the hypothetical. I feel that you're responding in bad faith."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "I don't have any faith. We're just running around in circles."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Can you... tell me your name, young lady?"

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "I'm Currer Bell."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Mz. Bell. I will spell it out for you. You would likely not be happy with how unsuitable your household is for avoiding fires. Please, take this pamphlet. It will do far more than I ever could when talking to someone like... *you*." He hands her one of his stock pamphlets that he takes from the nearby fire station.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: "Consider spreading these ideas in your place of work, as well. Although I somehow doubt you will heed my warnings, judging by your responses thus far."

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: The latter part is mumbled incredibly loudly.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: Not waiting for any response, he grabs an array of handheld fire extinguishers from his various pockets, the last few he has left for this month. He whirls around at the remaining park visitors he hasn't warded off. His sharp gaze tries to pick out anyone that looks unusually vulnerable.

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: Roll. Perception I suppose

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: v_entenmann
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\20b83a35b4910b5eb78d21e494ba8aac-2A6FD.png

messages.content: Viotto spots a few people who are especially vulnerable, but they are all children. He should think carefully before he goes through with anything.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
Viotto does not do this. There are times to think carefully, and right now is 'charisma time', not 'obsess over the specifics of your speeches time'. He walks up to a random child.

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

There's no reason somebody would just want to destroy my bedroom, too. So I can't see a good reason anything would've been placed to act on a short-term basis while necessitating the movement."

author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "It would still be possible that I was moved hours ago and they already left, but if the timing was right, I could easily catch them in the act now. author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She approaches the taxi and gets in.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Where will it be, old chum?" The Driver (TAP) asks this.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She reads the address aloud.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Ah, Danny." He mutters half to himself and then drives you there (this is his job (he's The Driver)).

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She starts another page: "stolen goods case", reception dated today, "payment given in advance", the address, and "residence of Danny?". As they arrive, she hands him the fare.* "I would like a receipt, please."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: The Driver painstakingly writes out a receipt, having no means to print one. It's a really great receipt, basically indistinguishable from the genuine mechanically produced article.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She gives him a look of slight amusement and folds and pockets the receipt.* "Thank you." *She then opens the door and leaves the car.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: These things happen. The street is a fairly well off part of the city, nice houses not far from commercial districts. Rikarasu is BY the house

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She knocks at the door.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: After some time, a muscular man with a goatee opens the door. "Ah. Fainda, I presume? It's good to see you. I'm Ryuki Kazuma."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She nods.* "Detective Fainda Shinjitsu. Are you my client?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Yeah. I have a uh... sensitive item missing. Please, come in."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She steps inside.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: Rikarasu.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She takes another step forward just for good measure.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Thanks."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She then looks towards him.* "A sensitive item missing? Please elaborate."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "It is..." He looks around him from side to side before continuing. "...a music box. It's been in my family for some time. I occasionally bring it in my coat pocket as a good luck charm, of sorts. It's not a very 'cool' thing, so I'd like to keep this quiet."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Your sensitivities are of no concern to me. To want to hide the truth out of shame is little different from sin."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Yes... perhaps I've been a fool."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She notes down "stolen item: music box", "family heirloom", "kept in coat pocket as good luck charm"  and turns to the next page. "Ryuki Kazuma", "client", "cares for appearances", "self-conscious", "possibly not upfront".*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She looks up at him again.* "For you to carry such an item in your coat pocket, I presume it would be of the smaller variety. When did you lose it?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I know I had it when I exited the train station, but I didn't when I entered my home. I really can't imagine it'd just fall out. I think someone took it."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Did this occur today?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "It was... yesterday, yeah. Close to midnight."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She turns back a page. Yesterday's date as the date of the crime, "close to 12:00 AM", "lost between exiting train station and arriving home".*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "A situation such as this presents you as the victim of common pickpocketry. For what reason were you at the train station, and how did you travel home? Did you have any suspicions at the time?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I was at a meeting. I used public transport to get there and back. I feel that I must've been close to home when I lost it, but that's just a gut instinct. There's people out there who don't like me, but I think they'd all resort to something more extreme if they wanted to screw with me in particular."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((For note, this house is only like three blocks away from the nearest train station. Rikarasu probably knows this))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Clarify. Is it correct that you boarded a train at the train station, arrived at the site of the meeting, attended the meeting, boarded another train to return, departed at the same train station, and walked back to this house from that point?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: Ryuki looks confused. "Uh. Yes."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She notes down "not clear about details", "has enemies" for Ryuki and "lost during quick walk back, possibly close to house", "occurred after trains were used to attend a meeting and return" on the page for the case.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She furrows her brows slightly.* "Did you pass by anyone at the time?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: Ryuki pauses to think. "It was late, so not many folks were out and about. I can't remember anyone in particular who was that close to me."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "This was apparently quite a discreet theft."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "If others would wish to spite you, it cannot yet be ruled out that your enemies aimed for exactly what would cut through to you the most. You were evidently willing to spend a significant sum for its search."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Is it also correct that the music box had little monetary value? Its only sizeable worth was personal attachment?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Yes, I believe so."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She writes down "music box has little value".* "Still relevant, in that case, is the question of how many people knew about the music box? Since you felt disinclined to flaunt it, I suspect you'd be able to name any others who you'd shown it to in the past."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: Ryuki is looking a little impatient, but not to the extent that he's blatantly being rude. "Sure, like, one guy saw me take it out once. But he didn't make a big deal of it."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Be more specific. If it was merely one guy, it should be of no inconvenience to elaborate."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: Ryuki thinks for a second. "...Souta. Guy works for me. Little bit uncomfortable to talk to."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She starts a new page for Souta. "uncomfortable to talk to", "works for Ryuki", "knew about the music box".*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "I believe the most pertinent questions of immediate significance have been asked. Show me the coat in question for examination."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: He takes off his coat which he is wearing, and hands it to you.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She snorts.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *Taking it, she looks down at it for a few seconds and then passes it back.* "That will be all. Are you willing to join me for the investigation?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Sure, I'm not busy."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She steps out of the house.* "Our first destination will be the train station. To stay on the path of any clues, I'd like you to retrace in reverse the precise route you took from the station yesterday."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
"Okay."

Ryuki steps out of his house.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She waits for him to move.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: Ryuki does the Dwayne The Rock Johnson eyebrow curl. "Souta?" He stares at a man standing adjacent to the house next door, who then begins to book it. "What?!"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *Fainda locks on to the man and immediately runs after him, going for a grab.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: ((roll athletics or acrobatics to catch up to him, then Grapple Contest))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: ((21 :peview:))

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: ((4 to grapple))

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: ((which is to say a nat 1,))

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: Rikarasu catches up to the man, but her hands slip off him and she loses her footing briefly. He is very greasy. Ryuki continues running ahead after him into an alleyway.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "Fff-ghrk!"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She straightens out her footing, pulls out her weapon, and continues running after the two.*

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: They successfully corner him, sure.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content:
Ryuki punches him in the face.

"You didn't have to actually [mumble mumble]", Souta says.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She glares at the two, aiming the weapon at Souta.* "What did he just say? Repeat that!"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: ((Roll intimidation))

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: Souta stammers. "Nothing, I just... I said he didn't have to actually for real hit me!" Ryuki stares at him.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What does that mean?" *She looks between them suspiciously.* "Explain yourself, sinner!"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
Souta. "I just... my fucking face hurts!"

"You're making me want to punch you even more." Ryuki sighs. "So... it's true, then. Kid, how much do you know about the lady who sent you here?"

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "...Me? Are you implying something?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "My referrer, who I know purely on terms of business, is of no relevance. I'm here for you as my client."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
Ryuki has a sad look in his eyes. "So, she would elect to..."

Souta. "Can I go back into the sewers now?"

Ryuki stares at him. "What? Yeah, sure, I guess. Why are you even still here? Do actually give me back my music box, though." He glares until his property is returned.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "What? The sewers?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "He lives there. It's a whole thing with him, don't ask. That was gonna be the whole thing, he stole from me by reaching up from a drain while I was sitting by the curb briefly. He wasn't supposed to just stand around outside my home like a dumbass."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "You knew this the entire time?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *She keeps her weapon fully trained on Souta.* "What do you mean to suggest about Ms. Tanaka? An elaborate deception? Answer me!"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content:
Ryuki. "Yes, I knew the entire time. I thought this was an eccentric ARG thing for a friend of hers, I didn't think she was actually..."

Souta. "Who the hell is Tanaka? I mean, I know guys with that name, but..."

Ryuki tells him to shut it. "I don't think it's my place to talk to you about this. I would suggest having a real conversation with your employer about your work."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: *Fainda jerks her weapon down and fires a warning shot to the ground.* "Ha! Bwahahahaha! Do you truly believe I don't know what's going on here?"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "Yeah, I do." Ryuki.

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: "An eccentric ARG? As if! With the payment I've been given, the only sinners in this mystery are you!"

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: "You keep using that word. I'm not really sure I get that."

author.name: scipe
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\0a858383a5c98e5e573e49bf3f2bdbe1-9F159.png

messages.content: *She coughs a few times.* "There is only one absolute truth. There can be no greater sin than to shun it for a lie."

author.name: pichuis
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\067a034b6637690fc6e7a1ce319ff6e2-B09A8.png

messages.content: ((rikarasu no way))

author.name: millionsmicroreives

messages.content:
I consider my options for a moment. How would he reply to this? If this were a work of fiction, I'd probably be around chapter 1, and that'd be his chapter 1 in Q&A. So all I have to do is fit the events of Q&A-MA-1 together with this message in my mind, and I should be able to figure out what to do.
**Erica's Logic**
Obviously I can't just grab any possibility straight from a later part of the story. I need to imagine the situation like what his route initially presents them to me as, and figure out all of the options. That way, I can figure them all out down to the right one. The first thing to think about is what would happen if *I* replied to this DM. No, in this context I should fully say it as a Direct Message. That conveys the way he phrases his logic better. Anyway, the obvious answer is that they'll download on a virus onto my computer. But how would they do that? They'd have to get me to click a link or something first, and... I guess the obvious comparison there is the Gyakuten Saiban 4 Official Complete Guide present in chapter 1. He's presented as a massive fan of this book initially, and yet his actual obsession is with The Tale of Apollo Justice. Clearly, what this represents is that DA got lazy and confused. That's what's most applicable here, because in order for me to click it, I would have to get lazy and confused. So, if I just answer and don't click anything weird, this would definitely be safe. And as Madakoe, it's obvious he would answer the message in case something interesting happened. So, naturally, I have to answer the direct message. But what do I answer with?

author.name: dontatmiss
author.avatarUrl: C:\Users\Aidan\Documents\TAP Reading Order\json version\ASSETS forma de json\9af032ce4be7a04ab3b8b8778b11faea-65DAD.png

messages.content:
**Erica's Logic Part 2**
Okay, so since this is the part 2, this is obviously where the equivalent to the first labyrinth chapter would be. If I'm trying to follow his actions here, he doesn't really do much that's all too applicable. If I could pointlessly kill RE three zero six zero six eight three eight eight five nine six eight six nine six, that would of course be the first choice. But I don't know where they live, and I don't know how to kill them. Kicking a door probably doesn't apply here either? I guess I'll have to be more broad here. Elfbat does something more applicable here, I guess? He's still awful, but he's at least no Bruum, so I'll try to tolerate him for a bit. He calls himself Mozart, which is a clear lie for a pseudonym. That probably works to make it clear I don't intend to get too personal, but I am listening. The DM wants to know my name, so it does match up pretty well. But, do I really want to copy Elfbat? I mean, Madakoe also uses a pseudonym, so I guess it makes sense to use one too. What did he call himself again, Belto Shelf? Shelk? Something like that. I consider opening Q&A back up to check, but that sounds fucking boring to get through none Madakoe scenes. I guess I should probably not copy Madakoe's pseudonym, I don't want to appear like a completely idiotic fangirl. So what should I use as a pseudonym that clearly matches both my tone, and what I intend to come across here. I guess in this case, this is also pretty similar to the contract from chapter 3. It was clearly suspicious, so that's probably fairly applicable here. If this is chapter 3, should I maybe jump to logic part 3? No, I don't really have much to say there. Okay. So right, Madakoe signs the contract with his own name. I obviously don't want to call myself Erica towards a total stranger, but I still want to follow his teachings here.

And if you’re gonna fire me for that, little lady, I’ll leave right now with my head held high.”

messages.content: “There’s not really any direct precedent for Madakoe, who is me, dealing with a hacker. The closest thing would be like, ||when that guy hacked into the gas trick to set everything on fire?|| But I wasn’t that relevant to all that nonsense. And I certainly didn’t catch the person who would be the ‘hacker’. I don’t actually remember what the hell the resolution to that was. ||My mind delusion of Pichuis(TToAJ4) was sort of related, though. He turned into like… the other gas trick, and tricked oil into dying.|| So I guess the answer would be to try to enlist the assistance of GassyNTricky? But he’s probably still asleep, and twitter’s probably still down. So instead… well, I got out of that mess as far as it was affecting me, Madakoe, directly, via ||the transformation of someone who originated as my vision of a fictional character||. So maybe, for Erica…”

𝙸𝚝’𝚜 𝚊𝚕𝚕 𝚝𝚑𝚊𝚝’𝚜 𝚛𝚎𝚕𝚎𝚟𝚊𝚗𝚝. 𝙸 𝚍𝚘𝚗’𝚝 𝚛𝚎𝚊𝚕𝚕𝚢 𝚗𝚎𝚎𝚍 𝚢𝚘𝚞𝚛 𝚊𝚌𝚝𝚞𝚊𝚕 𝚗𝚊𝚖𝚎 𝚎𝚒𝚝𝚑𝚎𝚛, 𝙸 𝚐𝚞𝚎𝚜𝚜. 𝙹𝚞𝚜𝚝 𝚠𝚑𝚊𝚝𝚎𝚟𝚎𝚛 𝚊𝚋𝚘𝚞𝚝 𝚠𝚑𝚘 𝚢𝚘𝚞 𝚊𝚛𝚎 𝚖𝚊𝚍𝚎 𝚝𝚑𝚒𝚜 𝚙𝚘𝚜𝚜𝚒𝚋𝚕𝚎.

𝙸𝚝’𝚜 𝚋𝚢 𝚗𝚘 𝚖𝚎𝚊𝚗𝚜 𝚊 𝚜𝚊𝚏𝚎 𝚊𝚜𝚜𝚞𝚖𝚙𝚝𝚒𝚘𝚗 𝚝𝚑𝚊𝚝 𝚂𝚘𝚞𝚕 𝚒𝚜𝚗’𝚝 𝚖𝚢 𝚊𝚌𝚝𝚞𝚊𝚕 𝚗𝚊𝚖𝚎, 𝚊𝚗𝚢𝚠𝚊𝚢. 𝙸𝚝 𝚒𝚜𝚗’𝚝, 𝚋𝚞𝚝 𝚝𝚑𝚎𝚛𝚎’𝚜 𝚙𝚎𝚘𝚙𝚕𝚎 𝚒𝚗 𝚝𝚑𝚒𝚜 𝚠𝚘𝚛𝚕𝚍 𝚠𝚒𝚝𝚑 𝚗𝚊𝚖𝚎𝚜 𝚕𝚒𝚔𝚎 “𝚉𝚊𝚚𝚞𝚎𝚛𝚊 𝙲𝚞𝚕𝚋𝚊𝚜𝚔𝚘” 𝚘𝚛 “𝙺𝚕𝚊𝚞𝚍 𝚁𝚎𝚊𝚌𝚝𝚒𝚘𝚗”. 𝚆𝚑𝚢 𝚗𝚘𝚝 𝚂𝚘𝚞𝚕?

𝙽𝚘, 𝚒𝚝’𝚜 𝚛𝚎𝚊𝚕. 𝙽𝚘𝚝 𝚊 𝚋𝚒𝚐 𝚍𝚎𝚊𝚕 𝚕𝚒𝚔𝚎 𝚝𝚑𝚎 𝚏𝚒𝚛𝚜𝚝, 𝚊𝚍𝚖𝚒𝚝𝚝𝚎𝚍𝚕𝚢. 𝙷𝚎 𝚙𝚛𝚘𝚋𝚊𝚋𝚕𝚢 𝚑𝚊𝚜 𝚊 𝙵𝚊𝚌𝚎𝚋𝚘𝚘𝚔 𝚘𝚛 𝙻𝚒𝚗𝚔𝚎𝚍𝙸𝚗 𝚘𝚛 𝚠𝚑𝚊𝚝𝚎𝚟𝚎𝚛.

𝙸 𝚜𝚞𝚙𝚙𝚘𝚜𝚎 𝚒𝚝 𝚠𝚊𝚜 𝚞𝚗𝚠𝚒𝚜𝚎 𝚝𝚘 𝚖𝚎𝚗𝚝𝚒𝚘𝚗 𝚔𝚗𝚘𝚠𝚒𝚗𝚐 𝚜𝚘𝚖𝚎𝚘𝚗𝚎 𝚠𝚒𝚝𝚑 𝚜𝚞𝚌𝚑 𝚊 𝚜𝚙𝚎𝚌𝚒𝚏𝚒𝚌 𝚗𝚊𝚖𝚎. 𝙱𝚞𝚝 𝙸 𝚠𝚎𝚕𝚌𝚘𝚖𝚎 𝚝𝚑𝚎 𝚊𝚞𝚝𝚑𝚘𝚛𝚒𝚝𝚒𝚎𝚜 𝚝𝚘 𝚝𝚛𝚢 𝚜𝚘𝚖𝚎𝚑𝚘𝚠 𝚐𝚎𝚝𝚝𝚒𝚗𝚐 𝚖𝚎 𝚠𝚒𝚝𝚑 𝚝𝚑𝚊𝚝. 𝙸𝚏 𝚝𝚑𝚎𝚢 𝚎𝚟𝚎𝚗 𝚍𝚘 𝚐𝚎𝚝 𝚒𝚝. 𝙷𝚘𝚗𝚘𝚛 𝚊𝚖𝚘𝚗𝚐 𝚝𝚑𝚒𝚎𝚟𝚎𝚜, 𝚊𝚗𝚍 𝚜𝚞𝚌𝚑. 𝙸 𝚍𝚘𝚗’𝚝 𝚙𝚕𝚊𝚗 𝚘𝚗 𝚝𝚎𝚕𝚕𝚒𝚗𝚐 𝚊𝚗𝚢𝚘𝚗𝚎 𝚎𝚕𝚜𝚎 𝚊𝚗𝚢𝚝𝚑𝚒𝚗𝚐 𝚢𝚘𝚞 𝚜𝚑𝚊𝚛𝚎 𝚠𝚒𝚝𝚑 𝚖𝚎.

messages.content:
𝙿𝚎𝚛𝚑𝚊𝚙𝚜 “𝚖𝚞𝚝𝚞𝚊𝚕𝚕𝚢 𝚊𝚜𝚜𝚞𝚛𝚎𝚍 𝚍𝚎𝚜𝚝𝚛𝚞𝚌𝚝𝚒𝚘𝚗” 𝚠𝚘𝚞𝚕𝚍 𝚋𝚎 𝚖𝚘𝚛𝚎 𝚊𝚙𝚝. 𝙸’𝚟𝚎 𝚓𝚞𝚜𝚝 𝚊𝚕𝚠𝚊𝚢𝚜 𝚋𝚎𝚎𝚗 𝚝𝚘𝚕𝚍 𝚝𝚘 𝚕𝚘𝚘𝚔 𝚊𝚝 𝚝𝚑𝚒𝚗𝚐𝚜 𝚏𝚛𝚘𝚖 𝚝𝚑𝚎 𝚋𝚛𝚒𝚐𝚑𝚝 𝚜𝚒𝚍𝚎.

𝙷𝚊𝚟𝚎 𝚢𝚘𝚞 𝚎𝚟𝚎𝚛 𝚐𝚘𝚗𝚎 𝚝𝚘 𝚝𝚛𝚒𝚊𝚕 𝚏𝚘𝚛 𝚏𝚊𝚋𝚛𝚒𝚌𝚊𝚝𝚎𝚍 𝚌𝚑𝚊𝚛𝚐𝚎𝚜 𝚘𝚏 𝚎𝚡𝚙𝚕𝚒𝚌𝚒𝚝 𝚖𝚊𝚝𝚎𝚛𝚒𝚊𝚕 𝚘𝚏 𝚌𝚑𝚒𝚕𝚍𝚛𝚎𝚗, 𝚂𝚝𝚊𝚗𝚐𝚒𝚘𝚝? 𝙸 𝚑𝚊𝚟𝚎𝚗’𝚝 𝚎𝚒𝚝𝚑𝚎𝚛, 𝚋𝚞𝚝 𝙸 𝚍𝚘𝚞𝚋𝚝 𝚒𝚝’𝚍 𝚋𝚎 𝚏𝚞𝚗 𝚏𝚘𝚛 𝚢𝚘𝚞.

messages.content:
𝙸’𝚕𝚕 𝚊𝚜𝚜𝚞𝚖𝚎 𝚢𝚘𝚞 𝚍𝚒𝚍𝚗’𝚝 𝚍𝚘 𝚒𝚝, 𝚝𝚑𝚎𝚗. 𝙸𝚗 𝚝𝚑𝚎 𝚠𝚘𝚛𝚜𝚝 𝚌𝚊𝚜𝚎 𝚜𝚌𝚎𝚗𝚊𝚛𝚒𝚘, 𝚒𝚝’𝚜 𝚗𝚘𝚝 𝚕𝚒𝚔𝚎 𝚎𝚡𝚙𝚕𝚊𝚒𝚗𝚒𝚗𝚐 𝚢𝚘𝚞𝚛 𝚘𝚠𝚗 𝚊𝚌𝚝𝚒𝚘𝚗𝚜 𝚝𝚘 𝚢𝚘𝚞 𝚠𝚘𝚞𝚕𝚍 𝚍𝚘 𝚊𝚗𝚢 𝚑𝚊𝚛𝚖, 𝚊𝚗𝚍 𝚘𝚝𝚑𝚎𝚛𝚠𝚒𝚜𝚎, 𝙸 𝚝𝚑𝚒𝚗𝚔 𝚢𝚘𝚞 𝚍𝚎𝚜𝚎𝚛𝚟𝚎 𝚏𝚊𝚒𝚛 𝚠𝚊𝚛𝚗𝚒𝚗𝚐.

𝚃𝚑𝚎 𝚠𝚎𝚋𝚜𝚒𝚝𝚎 𝚝𝚠𝚒𝚝𝚝𝚎𝚛.𝚌𝚘𝚖 𝚒𝚜 𝚍𝚘𝚠𝚗. 𝙱𝚎𝚎𝚗 𝚍𝚘𝚠𝚗 𝚏𝚘𝚛 𝚊 𝚋𝚒𝚝 𝚕𝚎𝚜𝚜 𝚝𝚑𝚊𝚗 𝚊𝚗 𝚑𝚘𝚞𝚛. 𝙽𝚘𝚝 𝚊𝚗 𝚎𝚗𝚝𝚒𝚛𝚎𝚕𝚢 𝚞𝚗𝚙𝚛𝚎𝚌𝚎𝚍𝚎𝚗𝚝𝚎𝚍 𝚘𝚌𝚌𝚞𝚛𝚛𝚎𝚗𝚌𝚎, 𝚊𝚗𝚍 𝚞𝚗𝚕𝚒𝚔𝚎 𝚖𝚎, 𝚝𝚑𝚒𝚜 𝚌𝚞𝚕𝚙𝚛𝚒𝚝 𝚍𝚒𝚍𝚗’𝚝 𝚠𝚊𝚗𝚝 𝚝𝚘 𝚋𝚕𝚊𝚛𝚎 𝚝𝚑𝚎𝚒𝚛 𝚒𝚍𝚎𝚗𝚝𝚒𝚝𝚢 𝚝𝚘 𝚝𝚑𝚎 𝚙𝚞𝚋𝚕𝚒𝚌. 𝙱𝚞𝚝 𝚋𝚎𝚑𝚒𝚗𝚍 𝚝𝚑𝚎 𝚜𝚌𝚎𝚗𝚎𝚜, 𝚝𝚑𝚎 𝚙𝚎𝚘𝚙𝚕𝚎 𝚠𝚑𝚘 𝚌𝚘𝚗𝚝𝚛𝚘𝚕 𝚝𝚑𝚎 𝚜𝚒𝚝𝚎 𝚊𝚛𝚎 𝚎𝚏𝚏𝚎𝚌𝚝𝚒𝚟𝚎𝚕𝚢 𝚋𝚎𝚒𝚗𝚐 𝚐𝚒𝚟𝚎𝚗 𝚊 𝚛𝚊𝚗𝚜𝚘𝚖. 𝚃𝚑𝚎𝚒𝚛 𝚝𝚠𝚘 𝚍𝚎𝚖𝚊𝚗𝚍𝚜 𝚠𝚎𝚛𝚎 𝚝𝚘 𝚞𝚗𝚋𝚊𝚗 𝚊𝚗 𝙸𝙿 𝚝𝚑𝚊𝚝 𝙸’𝚖 𝚜𝚝𝚒𝚕𝚕 𝚠𝚘𝚛𝚔𝚒𝚗𝚐 𝚘𝚗 𝚕𝚎𝚊𝚛𝚗𝚒𝚗𝚐 𝚖𝚘𝚛𝚎 𝚊𝚋𝚘𝚞𝚝, 𝚊𝚗𝚍 𝚙𝚛𝚎𝚟𝚎𝚗𝚝𝚒𝚗𝚐 @𝙼𝚊𝚍𝚊𝚔𝚘𝚎𝚂𝚝𝚊𝚗𝚐𝚒𝚘𝚝 𝚏𝚛𝚘𝚖 𝚋𝚎𝚒𝚗𝚐 𝚋𝚕𝚘𝚌𝚔𝚎𝚍 𝚋𝚢 𝚊𝚗𝚢𝚘𝚗𝚎, 𝚎𝚜𝚙𝚎𝚌𝚒𝚊𝚕𝚕𝚢 @𝙱𝚛𝚞𝚞𝚖𝚌𝚘𝚛𝚍𝚔𝚒𝚝𝚝𝚎𝚗.

𝙸 𝚝𝚑𝚒𝚗𝚔 𝚝𝚑𝚎𝚢 𝚖𝚊𝚢𝚋𝚎 𝚒𝚗𝚝𝚎𝚗𝚍𝚎𝚍 𝚝𝚘 𝚊𝚍𝚍 𝚖𝚘𝚛𝚎 𝚍𝚎𝚖𝚊𝚗𝚍𝚜 𝚝𝚘 𝚘𝚋𝚏𝚞𝚜𝚌𝚊𝚝𝚎 𝚝𝚑𝚎𝚒𝚛 𝚝𝚛𝚞𝚎 𝚖𝚘𝚝𝚒𝚟𝚎𝚜, 𝚋𝚞𝚝 𝚝𝚑𝚎𝚢 𝚓𝚞𝚜𝚝 𝚊𝚍𝚍𝚎𝚍 “𝚙𝚕𝚊𝚌𝚎𝚑𝚘𝚕𝚍𝚎𝚛” 𝚝𝚎𝚗 𝚝𝚒𝚖𝚎𝚜 𝚝𝚘 𝚝𝚑𝚎 𝚕𝚒𝚜𝚝 𝚘𝚏 𝚠𝚑𝚊𝚝 𝚝𝚑𝚎𝚢 𝚠𝚊𝚗𝚝𝚎𝚍 𝚝𝚘 𝚛𝚎𝚝𝚞𝚛𝚗 𝚝𝚑𝚎 𝚠𝚎𝚋𝚜𝚒𝚝𝚎 𝚝𝚘 𝚊 𝚏𝚞𝚗𝚌𝚝𝚒𝚘𝚗𝚒𝚗𝚐 𝚜𝚝𝚊𝚝𝚎.

messages.content:
𝚂𝚘𝚖𝚎𝚝𝚑𝚒𝚗𝚐’𝚜 𝚜𝚌𝚛𝚎𝚠𝚒𝚗𝚐 𝚠𝚒𝚝𝚑 𝚖𝚢 𝚊𝚋𝚒𝚕𝚒𝚝𝚢 𝚝𝚘 𝚐𝚎𝚝 𝚖𝚘𝚛𝚎 𝚜𝚙𝚎𝚌𝚒𝚏𝚒𝚌 𝚒𝚗𝚏𝚘𝚛𝚖𝚊𝚝𝚒𝚘𝚗, 𝚋𝚞𝚝 𝚢𝚘𝚞𝚛 𝚙𝚘𝚜𝚝𝚜 𝚜𝚎𝚎𝚖 𝚝𝚘 𝚒𝚖𝚙𝚕𝚢 𝚢𝚘𝚞’𝚛𝚎 𝚒𝚗 𝙶𝙼𝚃-𝟹, 𝚊𝚗𝚍 𝚢𝚘𝚞’𝚟𝚎 𝚞𝚜𝚎𝚍 𝚙𝚘𝚛𝚝𝚞𝚐𝚞𝚎𝚜𝚎 𝚋𝚎𝚏𝚘𝚛𝚎. 𝙳𝚘 𝚢𝚘𝚞 𝚔𝚗𝚘𝚠 𝚉𝚊𝚚𝚞𝚎𝚛𝚊? 𝙷𝚎’𝚜 𝚋𝚎𝚎𝚗 𝚝𝚑𝚎𝚛𝚎 𝚘𝚗 𝚘𝚌𝚌𝚊𝚜𝚒𝚘𝚗. 𝚃𝚑𝚊𝚝’𝚜 𝚝𝚑𝚎 𝚌𝚕𝚘𝚜𝚎𝚜𝚝 𝚝𝚑𝚒𝚗𝚐 𝚝𝚘 𝚊𝚗 𝚎𝚡𝚙𝚕𝚊𝚗𝚊𝚝𝚒𝚘𝚗 𝙸 𝚌𝚘𝚞𝚕𝚍 𝚑𝚊𝚟𝚎.

𝚆𝚎𝚕𝚕, 𝚗𝚎𝚟𝚎𝚛𝚖𝚒𝚗𝚍. 𝙸 𝚐𝚞𝚎𝚜𝚜 𝙸’𝚕𝚕 𝚏𝚒𝚗𝚍 𝚘𝚞𝚝 𝚜𝚘𝚘𝚗 𝚎𝚗𝚘𝚞𝚐𝚑. 𝙼𝚊𝚢𝚋𝚎 𝙸’𝚕𝚕 𝚋𝚎 𝚊𝚋𝚕𝚎 𝚝𝚘 𝚌𝚑𝚎𝚌𝚔 𝚝𝚑𝚎 𝚃𝙰𝙿 𝚛𝚎𝚐𝚒𝚜𝚝𝚛𝚢.

𝚈𝚘𝚞 𝚌𝚊𝚗 𝚑𝚊𝚟𝚎 𝚢𝚘𝚞𝚛 𝚌𝚘𝚖𝚙𝚞𝚝𝚎𝚛 𝚋𝚊𝚌𝚔. 𝙸’𝚖 𝚜𝚘𝚛𝚛𝚢 𝚝𝚘 𝚝𝚛𝚘𝚞𝚋𝚕𝚎 𝚢𝚘𝚞. 𝚃𝚑𝚘𝚞𝚐𝚑 𝚛𝚎𝚊𝚕𝚕𝚢, 𝚢𝚘𝚞 𝚖𝚊𝚢 𝚋𝚎 𝚍𝚒𝚜𝚊𝚙𝚙𝚘𝚒𝚗𝚝𝚎𝚍 𝚝𝚘 𝚏𝚒𝚗𝚍 𝚝𝚑𝚎 𝚠𝚎𝚋𝚜𝚒𝚝𝚎 𝚢𝚘𝚞 𝚕𝚘𝚘𝚔 𝚕𝚒𝚔𝚎 𝚢𝚘𝚞 𝚜𝚙𝚎𝚗𝚍 𝚠𝚊𝚢 𝚝𝚘𝚘 𝚖𝚞𝚌𝚑 𝚝𝚒𝚖𝚎 𝚘𝚗 𝚒𝚜 𝚜𝚝𝚒𝚕𝚕 𝚍𝚘𝚠𝚗. 𝙳𝚘𝚗’𝚝 𝚢𝚘𝚞 𝚑𝚊𝚟𝚎 𝚊𝚗𝚢𝚝𝚑𝚒𝚗𝚐 𝚋𝚎𝚝𝚝𝚎𝚛 𝚝𝚘 𝚍𝚘?

After a few minutes, Erica’s computer crashes again. It reboots to her normal startup screen.
